text: Good. Air quality is considered satisfactory, and air pollution poses little or no risk. Active children and adults, and people with respiratory disease, such as asthma, should limit prolonged outdoor exertion. You don't have to wear a mask. Breath and enjoy your day.

Good. Air quality is considered satisfactory, and air pollution poses little or no risk. Active children and adults, and people with respiratory disease, such as asthma, should limit prolonged outdoor exertion. You don't have to wear a mask. Breath and enjoy your day. "

Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups. Members of sensitive groups may experience health effects. The general public is not likely to be affected.  Active children and adults, and people with respiratory disease, such as asthma, should avoid prolonged outdoor exertion; everyone else, especially children, should limit prolonged outdoor exertion. We recommend wearing a surgical face mask for more sensitive people. They will block up to 80% of particles, which will help breathe and stay healthier.

Unhealthy. Everyone may begin to experience health effects; members of sensitive groups may experience more serious health effects. Active children and adults, and people with respiratory disease, such as asthma, should avoid all outdoor exertion; everyone else, especially children, should limit outdoor exertion. As the Air pollution is noticeable, we recommend wearing KF94 type of mask. It will reduce feelable unhealthy elements in the air and make it possible to work and study normally.

Very Unhealthy. Health warnings of emergency conditions. The entire population is more likely to be affected. At this level, air pollution is very unhealthy. We highly recommend N95 respirator masks, which will make it tolerable to be outside. While we would suggest you stay at home because of the pollution, this maks will help minimize the harmful effects of air quality.

Hazardous. Health alert: everyone may experience more serious health effects. Everyone should avoid all outdoor exertion. It is highly not recommended to be outdoor. The harmful impact of the low-quality air can damage the whole respiratory system and cause chronic diseases. However, having this all in mind, we recommend wearing a gas mask, which would cover the eyes, nose, and mouth in case of need to be outside.
